Privacy Policy
Last updated: January 2026

BeansDreams (“we”, “our”, or “us”) provides online services designed to help users manage and access their information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your data.

Information We Collect
• Information you provide directly, such as your name or email address.
• Information accessed through Google APIs (such as Sheets, Calendar, or Drive data), only with your explicit permission.
• Technical information such as IP address, browser type, and usage data.

How We Use Your Information
• To provide and improve our services.
• To personalize your experience.
• To communicate with you about updates or support.
• To operate features that require access to Google user data.

Google User Data
Our use of information received from Google APIs adheres to the Google API Services User Data Policy, including the Limited Use requirements.

Data Sharing
We do not sell or share your personal information with third parties except:
• When required by law.
• When necessary to operate our service (e.g., secure hosting providers).

Data Security
We use industry‑standard security measures to protect your information.

Your Choices
You may revoke access to your Google data at any time through your Google Account settings.

Contact Us
If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, contact us at:
support@beansdreams.org
